The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 ZTE Corp, Atlas ink $1-bn deal

 New Delhi, April 11 (PTI): ZTE Corporation, the Chinese telecom conglomerate, today signed an agreement with India?s telecom and broadband provider Atlas Interactive for a financial support of $1 billion.

 The agreement also involves a sales contract for $208 million, or Rs 850 crore, for the supply of 500,000 ports of asymmetric digital subscriber lines (ADSL), ZTE said in a release today. The agreement coincides with Chinese premier Wen Jiabao?s visit to India.

 Atlas Interactive is planning to acquire unified access licences for GSM, CDMA and fixed-line deployment in Delhi, Mumbai, Karnataka, Tamil Nadu, Madhya Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh (east and west), Bengal, Himachal Pradesh, Andhra Pradesh and Punjab. 




